01:34.390 --> 01:36.654
Hollywood:
Now, it has been a week.

01:36.690 --> 01:40.524
I paid $139
for expedited services.

01:40.560 --> 01:42.721
Now, where I'm from,
"expedited" means faster

01:42.770 --> 01:44.590
than your normal
slow-ass service.

01:44.630 --> 01:46.393
Yeah.

01:46.440 --> 01:47.862
Yeah, I hear you.

01:47.900 --> 01:49.401
Well, y'all need
to tighten up over there,

01:49.440 --> 01:50.907
is all I'm trying to say.

01:50.940 --> 01:52.373
( phone beeps off)

01:52.410 --> 01:54.628
What's that all about?

01:54.680 --> 01:57.672
Me and Leanne paid for
one of them quickie divorces.

01:57.710 --> 01:59.610
There ain't nothing
quick about it.

01:59.650 --> 02:02.414
And I can't pull up
on your aunt without
some proof.

02:02.450 --> 02:03.849
You ain't never lied.

02:06.190 --> 02:09.421
You know, I never really
even noticed it before.

02:09.460 --> 02:10.927
But you sitting
behind his desk,

02:10.960 --> 02:13.520
you look like your daddy
spit you right out.

02:16.470 --> 02:18.768
Got that same look
on your face and everything.

02:18.800 --> 02:22.668
What look's that?
Worry?

02:24.940 --> 02:26.532
I'll go and handle
this business.

02:26.580 --> 02:28.536
I'm going to holler at you
in a little while.

02:35.550 --> 02:37.313
( cell phone vibrates )

02:41.720 --> 02:43.654
Charley's voice:
Hi, you've reached
Charley Bordelon-West.

02:43.690 --> 02:44.918
I can't come to the phone
right now.

02:44.960 --> 02:46.552
Please leave a message.

02:46.600 --> 02:48.818
We got to figure out
this mill deal.

02:48.860 --> 02:52.535
We don't grind, that's
$1.5 million worth of cane

02:52.570 --> 02:54.731
just being left out to rot.

02:54.770 --> 02:56.635
Call me back, Charley.

02:58.840 --> 03:00.376
( phone beeps off)

03:06.980 --> 03:09.289
- What do you think?
- Too rislq.

03:09.320 --> 03:10.810
Good things
usually are.

03:10.850 --> 03:12.681
The equipment's
not up-to-date.

03:12.720 --> 03:14.312
That's not going
to cut it.

03:14.360 --> 03:15.884
Well, not now,
but I'll buy new equipment.

03:15.920 --> 03:17.751
You know,
I'll clean it up.

03:17.790 --> 03:21.351
Charley, that'll take you
at least six months to set up.

03:21.400 --> 03:23.368
By that time we will have
missed harvest.

03:23.400 --> 03:25.721
Come on, we can do it
in less time than that.

03:27.540 --> 03:28.734
How much is it?

03:30.640 --> 03:32.972
Owner says the Boudreauxs
are offering 8.

03:33.010 --> 03:37.208
But he said if I get
closer to 9, it's mine.

03:38.650 --> 03:40.311
But they want an offer
by the end of next week.

03:40.350 --> 03:41.647
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Wait.

03:42.820 --> 03:45.846
- Nine million dollars?
- Yeah.

03:45.890 --> 03:47.983
Charley, Farm and Loan
wouldn't lend you enough money

03:48.020 --> 03:49.624
to get through harvest.

03:49.660 --> 03:51.457
How are you going to come up
with $9 million in a week?

03:51.490 --> 03:52.798
I have an investor in mind.

03:52.830 --> 03:55.355
Frank Rovner,
the New Orleans Stingers owner.

03:55.400 --> 03:56.799
I'm meeting him
this afternoon.

03:56.830 --> 03:58.866
He'll go in for half.

03:58.900 --> 04:00.663
Hopefully.

04:02.410 --> 04:04.731
Tell me why.

04:04.770 --> 04:07.000
_ _Because this
IS beating the Boudreauxs
at their own game.

04:07.040 --> 04:08.473
They'll never
see this coming.

04:08.510 --> 04:10.341
So this is a revenge purchase?

04:10.380 --> 04:11.870
You said I needed
to go all in.

04:11.910 --> 04:13.912
Yeah, I meant
with the farm.

04:13.950 --> 04:16.510
But you know I'm not
a farmer, Remy.

04:16.550 --> 04:17.949
I'm a businesswoman.

04:17.990 --> 04:19.480
A CEO.

04:19.520 --> 04:22.353
Someone in control
of their own destiny.

04:22.390 --> 04:24.756
And what I plan to do
with this,

04:24.790 --> 04:26.496
is turn it into
my own busmess.

04:26.530 --> 04:27.952
Yeah, I'm sure the Durands

04:28.000 --> 04:31.299
had that the very same
thing in mind.

04:31.330 --> 04:33.935
This parish is littered
with abandoned mills,

04:33.970 --> 04:36.507
and people like you
who took on Goliath
and lost.

04:36.540 --> 04:39.407
No, I've taken on
bigger giants than
the Boudreauxs before.

04:39.440 --> 04:41.670
And won.

04:43.710 --> 04:46.440
And if you help me,

04:46.480 --> 04:49.711
maybe host a potluck
for some of those farmers
that I met before?

04:49.750 --> 04:52.651
Ah, here we go.

04:52.690 --> 04:54.089
- What?
- I'm going to be honest.

04:54.120 --> 04:55.656
Okay.

04:55.690 --> 04:57.988
Feeling a little bit used.

04:59.630 --> 05:00.927
- A little bit.
- ( scoffs )

05:00.960 --> 05:02.962
That's okay.
It's okay.

05:03.000 --> 05:05.560
We could talk about it
tonight over dinner and wine.

05:05.600 --> 05:09.434
- Remy Newell...
-Hm?

05:09.470 --> 05:12.678
Are you asking me out
on a date?

05:12.710 --> 05:14.974
Uh...yeah.

05:15.010 --> 05:16.773
I guess I am.

05:35.060 --> 05:36.721
- ( Keke laughing )
- Micah: Uh, what?

05:36.770 --> 05:38.863
- It's okay.
- You're positive?

05:38.900 --> 05:40.834
Yes.

05:40.870 --> 05:42.906
Also, Boogie wants you
to come to dinner,

05:42.940 --> 05:44.737
now that me and you
are a thing.

05:44.770 --> 05:47.534
So, wait, you and I
are like...?

05:48.910 --> 05:50.605
Aren't we?

05:52.080 --> 05:53.741
You kiss me
all the damn time.

05:53.780 --> 05:55.577
Yeah. Yeah.

05:55.620 --> 05:57.986
Okay.

05:58.020 --> 05:59.578
But, wait,
he's met me before.

05:59.620 --> 06:01.588
Why does he want me
to come over?

06:01.620 --> 06:03.451
Have you dated
a black girl before?

06:03.490 --> 06:05.720
Why are you
asking me this?

06:05.760 --> 06:07.489
- Because...
- Does It matter?

06:07.530 --> 06:09.395
You in the South now.

06:09.430 --> 06:12.797
When you date a black girl,
then you meet her daddy.

06:12.840 --> 06:16.606
He makes sure you got manners,
and put a little fear in you.

06:16.640 --> 06:19.507
Got it.

06:19.540 --> 06:22.907
I meant to ask you,
why do you call your dad
Boogie?

06:24.510 --> 06:26.774
Boogie's my stepdad.

06:26.820 --> 06:28.947
My real dad left me
when I was little.

06:28.980 --> 06:32.711
But Boogie's been way more
of a dad than he ever was.

06:37.830 --> 06:39.821
Have you, um...

06:39.860 --> 06:41.589
talked to your dad?

06:42.970 --> 06:44.119
No.

06:45.970 --> 06:48.894
I mean,
what's the point?

06:48.940 --> 06:50.931
So he can tell me_
that he's sorry agaIn?

06:53.680 --> 06:55.671
So he can tell me
that I don't understand?

06:58.250 --> 07:02.118
I mean, Keke,
he was sleeping with
prostitutes for years,

07:02.150 --> 07:03.811
acting like this
perfect dad.

07:03.850 --> 07:06.717
I don't even know
who he IS anymore.

07:09.220 --> 07:10.824
Micah, your dad loves you.

07:12.260 --> 07:14.820
And that stuff is just
between him and your mom.

07:14.860 --> 07:16.794
Okay, well,
it affected me too,

07:16.830 --> 07:19.025
so why do I have to
talk to him to make
him feel better?

07:20.970 --> 07:23.700
You're right.
You shouldn't.

07:27.640 --> 07:28.902
Come here.

07:30.250 --> 07:32.571
I'm sorry.

07:32.620 --> 07:35.544
I didn't mean to be all...

07:35.580 --> 07:37.582
No.

07:37.620 --> 07:40.987
Don't apologize
for saying what you feel.

07:51.730 --> 07:53.197
( laughs )

07:58.540 --> 08:01.100
You sure you can't
come over after school?

08:01.140 --> 08:04.143
Not if I want
to pass Calculus.

08:04.180 --> 08:06.614
Let me help you study
for Calculus then.

08:06.650 --> 08:08.868
You sure you remember?

08:08.920 --> 08:11.241
You've been out of school
for a while now.

08:11.290 --> 08:13.588
- I'm think it'll all come back.
-(laughs)

08:13.620 --> 08:15.588
You know, once we start
it'll start to--

08:15.620 --> 08:17.281
All right.

08:17.330 --> 08:19.025
( cell phone vibrates )

08:19.060 --> 08:21.290
Hey, Nova. What's up?

08:21.330 --> 08:22.888
Nova over phone:
It's me and Rah.

08:22.930 --> 08:24.659
Hey, where are you guys?

08:24.700 --> 08:26.793
At my place.

08:26.840 --> 08:29.764
He came by to tell me about
this really impressive idea
he has for the harvest,

08:29.810 --> 08:31.801
without a Landry
or Boudreaux in sight.

08:31.840 --> 08:33.000
Hey, Charley.

08:33.040 --> 08:35.201
Can't call me back?

08:35.240 --> 08:37.640
I went out to St._ James.
They real nice.

08:37.680 --> 08:38.772
We could grind with them.

08:38.810 --> 08:40.277
No, St. James is too far.

08:40.320 --> 08:41.878
It is.

08:41.920 --> 08:43.217
But I researched
a truckIng company

08:43.250 --> 08:45.138
that leases out refrigerated
trucks, you know,

08:45.190 --> 08:46.885
for like produce and stuff.

08:46.920 --> 08:49.889
We could haul
our cane In that,

08:49.930 --> 08:51.750
that way the sugar
and the cane don't
crystallize,

08:51.790 --> 08:53.155
and we shouldn't be out
nothing except, what,

08:53.200 --> 08:54.758
the trucks
and the diesel costs,

08:54.800 --> 08:56.097
which ain't cheap,

08:56.130 --> 08:57.563
but what other choice
we got?

08:57.600 --> 08:58.919
I told you I'm handling it,
Ralph Angel.

08:58.970 --> 09:00.892
You didn't sign anything?

09:00.940 --> 09:03.158
No, but I want to.
That's the point.

09:03.210 --> 09:05.098
I told you to wait.

09:05.140 --> 09:06.676
Aren't we partners?

09:06.710 --> 09:08.632
I mean,
maybe if you listen--

09:08.680 --> 09:10.568
I'm working on something.

09:10.610 --> 09:12.669
I told you, I've got it
handled, you guys.

09:12.720 --> 09:14.847
Just let me get things
in order. I've got to go,
okay? Bye-bye.

09:14.880 --> 09:16.108
Hi.

09:16.150 --> 09:17.686
Come on.
( phone signal beeps )

09:17.720 --> 09:19.210
I know she didn't just
hang up.

09:19.250 --> 09:20.854
Yeah, she did.

09:20.890 --> 09:23.256
Ain't nothing new,
though.

09:23.290 --> 09:24.723
If she don't come up
with the idea,

09:24.760 --> 09:26.352
she don't want
to hear about it.

09:26.390 --> 09:28.790
At least she picked up
your phone call.

09:28.830 --> 09:31.594
She sent me straight
to voicemail.

09:31.630 --> 09:32.790
I'll get into it.

09:32.840 --> 09:34.091
Mm-hmm.

09:34.140 --> 09:35.698
That's a pretty damn
goodidea.

09:35.740 --> 09:37.901
Good thinking.

09:39.270 --> 09:41.579
I'm proud of you.

09:43.010 --> 09:44.238
Appreciate that.

09:55.260 --> 09:56.386
Frank:
Charley.

09:56.420 --> 09:57.751
- Frank.
- ( Frank chuckles )

09:57.790 --> 09:59.382
- How are you?
- I'm well.

09:59.430 --> 10:01.227
- How's your son?
- He's doing well.

10:01.260 --> 10:03.399
Good. Uh, please.

10:03.430 --> 10:04.727
Thanks.

10:04.770 --> 10:07.136
You want some water, or--?

10:07.170 --> 10:09.092
I'll have what you're having.
But I'll take it neat.

10:09.140 --> 10:10.835
You're a woman
after my own heart.

10:10.870 --> 10:12.360
( laughs )

10:12.410 --> 10:14.037
So, I think Davis

10:14.080 --> 10:16.844
would consider coming
to play for the Stingers

10:16.880 --> 10:18.006
_ if the offer
IS competitive.

10:18.050 --> 10:21.110
I told you, a marquee
player like Davis

10:21.150 --> 10:24.142
is too rich for my blood.

10:24.190 --> 10:28.012
IfI could arrange
a sit-down with Davis,

10:28.060 --> 10:29.789
would you hear
my proposal?

10:31.790 --> 10:34.156
Tell me this, honestly.

10:34.200 --> 10:37.727
Would Davis West
throw down 25, 30 points
a game

10:37.770 --> 10:40.989
without Felix Evans
feeding him the assists?

10:41.040 --> 10:44.908
Because before Felix
got to the Gladiators,

10:44.940 --> 10:47.431
Davis wasn't putting up
those kind of stats.

10:47.480 --> 10:51.871
So you're saying
you'd like them both?

10:51.910 --> 10:54.447
I'm saying
that's not an option.

10:54.480 --> 10:58.018
Felix and Davis have all but
signed on the dotted line

10:58.050 --> 11:01.053
to play together
in New York.

11:01.090 --> 11:03.820
Well, you can't compete
unless you make an offer.

11:06.490 --> 11:08.299
I'm meeting
with Felix tomorrow,

11:08.330 --> 11:10.890
ifI can get his agent
to quit jerking me around.

11:10.930 --> 11:12.022
( laughs )

11:12.070 --> 11:13.469
And Davis?

11:13.500 --> 11:15.331
( sighs )

11:15.370 --> 11:18.237
Respectfully, Charley,

11:18.270 --> 11:20.807
do you have the access
and the approvals

11:20.840 --> 11:23.308
to even negotiate
on Davis's behalf?

11:23.350 --> 11:25.238
The access?

11:25.280 --> 11:27.817
He's my husband, Frank.

11:27.850 --> 11:30.318
That answer
should be obvious.

11:30.350 --> 11:31.681
And the approvals?

11:33.260 --> 11:36.354
I am the approval.

11:36.390 --> 11:38.051
Always have been.

11:38.090 --> 11:39.955
Nothing's changed
in that department.

11:41.500 --> 11:43.491
Charley, you don't have
to rush out.

11:43.530 --> 11:46.260
No, I see I have something
to prove to you.
But that's okay.

11:46.300 --> 11:49.133
I've been underestimated
before.

11:51.240 --> 11:52.366
Hmm!

11:53.840 --> 11:55.068
It's always a great
vantage point

11:55.110 --> 11:57.476
in negotiations, am I right?

11:57.510 --> 11:58.977
Have a good day, Frank.

12:09.290 --> 12:09.517
( sighs )

12:17.200 --> 12:20.363
Hey, I didn't
hear you come in.

12:20.400 --> 12:22.129
Blue's asleep.

12:25.140 --> 12:26.869
What's wrong?

12:28.280 --> 12:30.840
Just Charley.

12:30.880 --> 12:33.542
Same old, same old.

12:33.580 --> 12:37.289
Won't let me do anything,
say nothing.

12:37.320 --> 12:39.242
It's all her,

12:39.290 --> 12:42.987
all the time.

12:43.030 --> 12:47.126
Can't even do nothing
without her permission.

12:47.160 --> 12:49.822
Like she running
this farm and not me.

12:54.070 --> 12:56.265
You're the one taking care
of this place.

12:56.300 --> 12:57.528
But she don't see that.

12:57.570 --> 13:00.130
It doesn't matter
what she does.

13:00.180 --> 13:02.978
All th is you.

13:04.910 --> 13:08.016
You're the one up at dawn
planting and weeding

13:08.050 --> 13:11.178
and taking care of this place
day after day after day.

13:13.190 --> 13:16.785
You've accomplished so much
around here, Ralph Angel.

13:20.530 --> 13:22.521
Your daddy would be
so proud of you.

13:30.610 --> 13:32.532
I'm proud of you.

13:35.410 --> 13:37.503
You know what you've done,
and that's all that matters.

14:19.650 --> 14:22.187
( phone rings )

14:23.460 --> 14:24.620
Lena over phone:
Hello?

14:24.660 --> 14:26.082
Hi, Lena.

14:26.130 --> 14:27.552
It's Charley.
How are you?

14:27.600 --> 14:30.262
Oh, my God, Charley.
So good to hear your voice.

14:30.300 --> 14:33.360
I heard a little rumor
that you might be in town.

14:33.400 --> 14:35.436
You know I'm living
just outside of New Orleans,
right?

14:35.470 --> 14:37.301
I forgot your family
was living out here.

14:37.340 --> 14:38.659
I got a sister here, too.

14:38.710 --> 14:40.575
I remember.
You staying with her?

14:40.610 --> 14:42.976
No, Felix and I
are staying at The W.

14:43.010 --> 14:44.671
You know how it is
staying with family.

14:44.710 --> 14:46.507
They think you're bougie
because you like espresso

14:46.550 --> 14:48.518
and your own bathroom.

14:48.550 --> 14:49.642
( Lena laughs )

14:49.680 --> 14:51.113
( laughing )

14:51.150 --> 14:52.913
Right, right.

14:52.960 --> 14:54.655
So, while you're in town,
we should get dinner.

14:54.690 --> 14:55.987
You know, catch up.

14:56.020 --> 14:57.658
Oh, Felix and I
are leaving tomorrow.

14:57.690 --> 14:59.999
Oh, perfect.
We can go out tonight.

15:00.030 --> 15:01.258
Just us girls.

15:01.300 --> 15:02.653
Okay.

15:02.700 --> 15:04.395
That-- That would be great,
Charley.

15:04.430 --> 15:07.263
I'll come to you.
Hotel bar, 7-ish?

15:07.300 --> 15:08.494
Can't wait.

15:23.190 --> 15:24.646
( door opens )

15:27.460 --> 15:29.314
- Hey, Aunt Vi,
- Violet: Hey, you.

15:30.590 --> 15:32.421
Smells good.

15:32.460 --> 15:34.496
That for me or Hollywood?

15:34.530 --> 15:36.157
( chuckles )

15:36.200 --> 15:39.419
Well, I admit, I drove by
earlier this morning

15:39.470 --> 15:41.199
and saw his truck.

15:41.240 --> 15:42.434
I didn't think
he was coming back

15:42.470 --> 15:44.734
from the rig
until Saturday.

15:44.770 --> 15:47.568
I thought I'd drop by,
say hello.

15:47.610 --> 15:51.068
Got back a few days ago.

15:51.110 --> 15:52.509
Sorry, he got back when?

15:52.550 --> 15:55.474
A few days ago.
'Wood, you got a visitor.

16:04.230 --> 16:06.084
Hey, Vi.

16:06.130 --> 16:08.690
I thought I smelled
your macaroni and cheese.

16:10.230 --> 16:13.097
Hollywood,

16:13.140 --> 16:15.734
you've been back
almost a week

16:15.770 --> 16:18.603
and you ain't thought
to stop by?

16:18.640 --> 16:21.108
Not to the High Yellow,
or my house?

16:22.240 --> 16:25.209
( no audible dialogue )

16:25.250 --> 16:27.969
- Baby, I can explain.
- Don't bother.

16:29.650 --> 16:31.345
Come on, Aunt Vi.

16:31.390 --> 16:33.085
Aunt Vi.

16:33.120 --> 16:34.485
( door opens )

16:34.520 --> 16:36.317
- My bad, 'Wood--
- ( door closes )

16:39.130 --> 16:40.392
- Vi!
- Don't, Hollywood.

16:40.430 --> 16:42.022
I'm late for work.

16:42.060 --> 16:43.596
Hollywood:
Come on, Vi.

16:45.200 --> 16:47.259
( car starts )

16:47.300 --> 16:51.532
